**Munmun Dutta** is an Indian film and television actress and model.[1] She
plays [Babita
Iyer](/wiki/List_of_Taarak_Mehta_Ka_Ooltah_Chashmah_characters#Babita_Krishnan_Iyer
"List of Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah characters") in the long-running
Hindi sitcom _[Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah
Chashmah](/wiki/Taarak_Mehta_Ka_Ooltah_Chashmah "Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah
Chashmah")_.[2]

## Early Life and
Education[[edit](/w/index.php?title=Munmun_Dutta&action=edit&section=1&editintro=Template:BLP_editintro
"Edit section: Early Life and Education")]

Dutta completed a Masters degree in English.[3] While living in Pune, Dutta
participated in fashion shows. She came to Mumbai and had her acting debut in
[Zee TV](/wiki/Zee_TV "Zee TV")'s 2004 serial _[Hum Sab
Baraati](/wiki/Hum_Sab_Baraati "Hum Sab Baraati")_. Her first film role was in
[Kamal Haasan](/wiki/Kamal_Haasan "Kamal Haasan")'s _[Mumbai
Express](/wiki/Mumbai_Express "Mumbai Express")_. In 2006, she appeared in the
film _[Holiday](/wiki/Holiday_\(2006_film\) "Holiday \(2006 film\)")_. She
also expressed her desire to become a doctor.[4]

## Other
works[[edit](/w/index.php?title=Munmun_Dutta&action=edit&section=2&editintro=Template:BLP_editintro
"Edit section: Other works")]

Dutta has been actively involved in social causes. Recently, she wrote an open
letter to the [Indian Education System](/wiki/Education_in_India "Education in
India") criticizing education patterns of India. She has also been sponsoring
education for her hair dresser's daughter and also her house-help.[5]
